gomodel:SYNGO_3759  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3. Tissue-Specific Syntaxin 4 Deletion Causes a Decrease in Both AMPAR-\nand NMDAR-Mediated fEPSPs as assessed in dendritic fEPSP recordings from CA1 neurons of control and syntaxin 4 cKO mice.\nFigure 4. Amplitude, but Not Frequency, of Spontaneous EPSCs of CA1 Pyramidal Neurons Is Reduced upon Syntaxin 4 cKO.\nFigure 5. Loss of Syntaxin 4 Leads to Reduced Surface Expression of Glutamate\nReceptors in Cultured Hippocampal Neurons. Experimental description: M&M: We purchased C57/B6-derived ESCs (HEPD0610_3_G07) with KO cassettes\nin one allele of the syntaxin 4 gene (syntaxin 4 GLT) from the European Condi-\ntional Mouse Mutagenesis Program (EUCOMM) and generated syntaxin 4 GLT\nmice. Syntaxin 4 GLT mice were crossed with FLP mice to\ncreate syntaxin 4 +/flox mice. CaMK2a-Cre mice were used to generate tis-\nsue-specific syntaxin 4 cKO mice." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3759" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

